<HEADLINE>
SELANNE IS CONSISTENT
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GREG CHRISTENSEN  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM -- Heading into Friday's game, Teemu Selanne had played
231 games with both the Mighty Ducks and Winnipeg Jets. His
production has been amazingly similar.
</P>
<P>
   Selanne scored 147 goals, 306 points and eight hat tricks for
the Jets. He scored 151 goals, 303 points and seven hat tricks in
his first 231 games for Anaheim.
</P>
<P>
   --
</P>
<P>
   Jaime Pushor, who has missed six games with a bruised left
shoulder, said he's eager to play again.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm feeling a lot better each day, said Pushor, who was hurt
Feb. 14 in Phoenix. ``It's up to the coaches, I think I'm ready to
play.
</P>
<P>
   ``I know a lot of guys aren't 100 percent and they are playing
hard, so it's frustrating.
</P>
<P>
   Pushor said he has regained full range of motion and ``it's just
a matter of getting the strength back.
</P>
<P>
   --
</P>
<P>
   Friday's sellout crowd of 17,174 was the first in 10 games at
the Pond. The Ducks hadn't sold out a game since Jan. 10 when they
played Edmonton. It was only Anaheim's fifth sellout in 30 home
dates this season. Last year the Ducks sold out 25 of 40 games.
</P>
<P>
   --
</P>
<P>
   As the season has progressed rookie Johan Davidsson's ice time
had slowly been reduced, especially since the Ted Drury and Jeff
Nielsen began to catch the eye of Ducks coach Craig Hartsburg.
</P>
<P>
   Rather than have Davidsson be scratched or play on the fourth
line, Anaheim opted to send the 23-year old forward to Cincinnati
of the AHL where he's expected to get plenty of playing time.
</P>
<P>
   Davidsson had scored three goals and seven points in 51 games
with the Ducks.
</P>
<P>
   Replacing Davidsson on the Anaheim roster is Mike Leclerc, who
had scored 19 goals and 43 points in Cincinnati before being
recalled.
</P>
<P>
   Leclerc, 22, has played in 14 NHL games, scoring one goal and
two points.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
