<SLUG> BC-BKN-RODMAN-SPI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
L.A. WARMS TO RODMAN GEEK SHOW 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By JIM MOORE  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ It won't be long until he is in Las Vegas,
but Friday night Dennis Rodman was gamboling at the Forum, creating
problems for the Los Angeles Clippers.
</P>
<P>
   Next week, next month, perhaps even tomorrow, the Los Angeles
Lakers might be wondering why they signed him, when Rodman is AWOL.
</P>
<P>
   For one evening at least, he was the purple-and-golden boy,
praised by the Dennis disciples, of which there are many in this
town.
</P>
<P>
   ``L.A. likes people who are unique, who have style and are
controversial,'' said Robert Shapiro, a member of O.J. Simpson's
legal team.
</P>
<P>
   ``He fits all of the criteria.''
</P>
<P>
   Another courtsider, actress Cathy Lee Crosby, supported the
signing by commenting on the machismo shown by the Lakers' owner.
</P>
<P>
   ``Jerry Buss has more (guts) than anybody I know,'' she said.
``He lives life the way he wants to live it. Things were like,
stale. He had to take chances. So he cracked it wide open.''
</P>
<P>
   And this is what's inside, a power forward who grabs headlines
and rebounds, a zero in some circles, hero in others. All will
agree that Dennis Rodman is unusual, and that's what kind of night
it was.
</P>
<P>
   Rodman did not score but was effective in other areas _ pulling
down 11 rebounds and distributing six assists. Several were
touchdown passes from baseline to baseline, finding open teammates
for layins. Rodman could not be located for post-game comments, but
that didn't matter.
</P>
<P>
   ``He speaks in jibberish and it's laced with profanity,'' said
one reporter familiar with the man.
</P>
<P>
   The game between the cross-town rivals was not as captivating as
the antics of the cross-dresser. Everyone wanted a glimpse of the
man _ to know when he arrived and how he appeared.
</P>
<P>
   His hair color was conservative for him _ black with blond
splotches, a fingerpainting in progress.
</P>
<P>
   Carmen Electra, Rodman's wife, was at his news conference on
Tuesday, a Beverly Hills event that kicked off geek week in which
Rodman discussed the topic of fondling along with his projected
status as a Laker.
</P>
<P>
   In the locker room before the game, Rodman never appeared while
the reporters lurked. But Shaquille O'Neal was there, trying on his
new size 22s while fielding questions about Kurt Rambis, who went
from interim coach to maximum madness. The former Laker player is
now the permanent Laker coach, for awhile anyway.
</P>
<P>
   ``I hated him,'' Shaq said of Rambis, the player. ``I thought he
was a dirty player. I remember his ugly glasses, the long hair ...
Clark Kent.''
</P>
<P>
   Rodman's locker remained vacant. It sits at the end of a row,
three removed from O'Neal's. Unassuming Travis Knight sits right
next door.
</P>
<P>
   ``He will be a bad role model for Travis,'' said Kobe Bryant,
laughing. ``Travis is a clean-cut Connecticut Husky.''
</P>
<P>
   A clean cut to Rodman is a precise tattoo if there is any room
left on that billboard body of his.
</P>
<P>
   ``Is Dennis here yet?'' O'Neal asked an hour before tipoff.
</P>
<P>
   Yes, he was told by Laker spokesman John Black. Rodman was busy
in the back, lifting weights. A FOX crew took video footage of his
empty locker, shooting Rodman's new jersey hanging on the rack.
</P>
<P>
   As reporters left the locker room, fans shuffled in but never
filled the Forum. Rodman can be fashionably late here.
</P>
<P>
   Fifteen minutes before gametime, the moment arrived. The
anticipation was about to end. Layup drills were about to begin. In
came Rodman, confidently trotting like always. He was greeted with
cheers and shot layups while fans stood, trying to get a view of
the newest Laker.
</P>
<P>
   Six minutes into the game, fans grew anxious, wanting their
first legitimate Rodman sighting. They chanted his name, and Rambis
obliged, inserting Rodman.
</P>
<P>
   ``This place will go wild as soon as he is introduced,'' Shapiro
predicted, and he was right.
</P>
<P>
   Rodman produced. In the first 30 seconds, he tapped a loose ball
to O'Neal for a layin. In the next 30 seconds, he pulled down an
offensive rebound and dished to O'Neal for a three-point play. In
one minute, the Laker lead went from 13-11 to 18-11.
</P>
<P>
   After the game, Rodman left the floor as fans reached down from
the stands, hoping for acknowledgment or, better yet, his jersey.
But Electra got that and clutched it during an interview.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was kind of funny at first,'' she said. ``I'm so used to
seeing him as a Bull. He's happy to be playing here.''
</P>
<P>
   Asked about something else, presumably a private subject,
Electra said: ``We don't talk about basketball very much. ... Every
time we're in Vegas, he runs around the hotel room naked.''
</P>
<P>
   Rodman is a fascinating freak who elicits emotions, good and
bad. There is no gray area with Rodman _ his world is black and
white and turquoise and forest green. In other words, he will be
comfortable here.
</P>
<P>
   ``L.A.,'' said Shapiro, ``is the place for Dennis Rodman.''
</P>
</TEXT>
