<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Saturday, Feb. 27, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Stew Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   LA-SWEEP (Los Angeles) _ Upset by new street sweeping rules that
force many neighborhoods to move parked cars twice a week,
thousands of residents are fighting to remove the signs and argue
the city cares more about the resultant parking tickets than
cleaning streets. By Greg Gittrich. (Will move in the ``n''
California news file.)
</P>
<P>
   CARD-KID (Los Angeles) _ Sason Dardashti borrowed $3 from a
friend, bought a pack of Michael Jordan basketball cards and scored
the card collector's equivalent of a full-court shot _ a rare card
with a piece of Jordan's jersey in it. The 12-year-old boy has
already turned down an offer of $1,200 for the card, which is part
of a fairly new trend of putting a piece of great athletes in a
card, from slivers of a Babe Ruth bat to Dan Marino's football
jersey. Phil Davis. (Will move in the ``n'' California news file.)
</P>
