444-8286.
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Phoenix) _ Police officers are taught to leave the
job at the precinct. To file it, lock it up, forget about it. Or
it'll overwhelm you. Part of that job, though _ the most important
part _ is saving lives. Luckily for a kid named Rocky, and for all
of us, there's one cop in town who decided to bring his work home
with him. By E.J. MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K''
categories.
