<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-RAC-SANTAANITA-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TUZLA CRUISES TO VICTORY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By GREG CHRISTENSEN  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ARCADIA _ Trainer Julio Canani is the excitable type. His prize
mare, Tuzla, suffers from ulcer problems.
</P>
<P>
   But neither Canani or Tuzla had any reason to be nervous on
Saturday as Tuzla cruised to an easy victory in the $150,000 Buena
Vista Handicap at Santa Anita.
</P>
<P>
   ``Even you could have ridden her today,'' joked Canani to a
passenger on the elevator taking the trainer down to track level
after Tuzla won for the fifth time in her last six starts.
</P>
<P>
   Canani was just stating the facts, not taking anything away from
Corey Nakatani's ride. The jockey dropped Tuzla into perfect
position _ third most of the way _ before making his move midway
through the final turn.
</P>
<P>
   ``She's a good (mare) and a great miler,'' said Canani of Tuzla,
which went off a 3-5 favorite in the 1-mile Grade II race on the
turf.
</P>
<P>
   Tuzla, which paid $3.40, $2.60 and $2.10, handed defending
champion Dance Parade her first defeat in four races on the Santa
Anita turf course.
</P>
<P>
   Dance Parade finished fourth in the five-horse field in her
first start since finishing sixth in the Hong Kong International on
Dec. 13, the same date Tuzla won the Grade II Dahlia Handicap at
Hollywood Park.
</P>
<P>
   Supercilious finished second, 2 1/2 lengths behind Tuzla and a
neck in front of Green Jewel. Supercilious paid $4.60 and $2.40.
Green Jewel $2.40 to show.
</P>
<P>
   Green Jewel led the majority of the race, but the result was
never in doubt.
</P>
<P>
   ``A mile is her best distance,'' said Canani. ``Today there was
no pace, but she showed she was the best.''
</P>
<P>
   Tuzla is good enough that Nakatani got out of his sick bed to
ride the 5-year old.
</P>
<P>
   ``She's a special filly and Julio has done such a great job with
her,'' said the jockey, who has been suffering from the flu. ``He
really knows her game, and whenever she's fresh she runs very big
races.''
</P>
<P>
   Canani says Tuzla enjoys long breaks between races and he has no
plans to change his methods. The trainer hopes to run Tuzla 6-8
times this year. He wouldn't be specific about any of his plans,
but admitted that a 1 3/8-mile race wouldn't be a good distance for
his mare. That might rule Tuzla out of the new $1 million Breeders
Cup Fillies and Mares Turf which will be run at that length.
</P>
<P>
   ``We are going to play it by ear,'' said Canani. ``We don't have
to run too much early in the year, you don't want to cook them this
early.''
</P>
<P>
   After all, Canani has a good thing on his hands, especially
since he and Nakatani have calmed Tuzla down.
</P>
<P>
   ``Early in her career she was really high-tempered and tough to
rate ... I've taken a lot of time and tried to get her to rate,''
said Nakatani of Tuzla, who is on medication for her ulcer and now
has a goat (Vincente) to pal around with. ``But one of the big
things is Julio has taken so much time with her ... I think she'll
definitely be the top turf mare in the country.''
</P>
</TEXT>
