   ``We came out flat in the second half, with no defense,'' said
Jeryl Sasser, who had 18 points and 10 rebounds in a losing effort.
``It seemed like we were satisfied just being in the tournament and
figured all we had to do to beat Rice was show up.
</P>
<P>
   ``We should have been hungry, because getting the three-seed was
our goal, but it didn't happen.''
</P>
