   For SMU, a 38-28 edge on the boards was almost useless because
of poor shooting. In the second half, the Mustangs shot 26 per cent
from the floor and 43 per cent from the free-throw line. For the
game, they were 34.5 percent from the floor and made barely half
their free throws.
</P>
